<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-16T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-16T06:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5049: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-16T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 16,
                                        1919—12 noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 11:25
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>2808. Following from [<persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName> at]
                            Archangel.</p>
                        <p>“1380, August 15th, 2 p.m. One thousand of the 1,200 Italian troops at
                            Murmansk are now embarked for repatriation. <persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName>.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJW1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>